        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 2:59PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 259 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bull City, or 12 miles northeast of Holt, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake View, Brookwood, Vance, Tannehill Ironworks State Park, Mercedes
Benz Of Alabama, Abernant, North Bibb, Caffee Junction, Bucksville,
and East Brookwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
